  "body": "Reproduction: create a project with a simple contract:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract Foo {\r\n  uint public x;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nand this deployment script:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst hre = require(\"hardhat\");\r\n\r\nasync function main() {\r\n  const signer = await ethers.getSigner();\r\n\r\n  // impersonate\r\n  const address = \"0x10A19e7eE7d7F8a52822f6817de8ea18204F2e4f\"\r\n  await hre.network.provider.request({ method: 'hardhat_impersonateAccount', params: [address] });\r\n  await signer.sendTransaction({ to: address, value: ethers.utils.parseEther(\"1\") })\r\n  const impersonatedSigner = await ethers.getSigner(address)\r\n\r\n  // deploy\r\n  const factory = await ethers.getContractFactory(\"Foo\", impersonatedSigner);\r\n  const deployment = await factory.deploy();\r\n  await deployment.deployTransaction.wait();\r\n\r\n  // check deployed code\r\n  console.log(await ethers.provider.getCode(deployment.address));\r\n}\r\n\r\nmain()\r\n  .then(() => process.exit(0))\r\n  .catch(error => {\r\n    console.error(error);\r\n    process.exit(1);\r\n  });\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd run `hh run deploy.js`. The string printed is `0x`. Changing `impersonatedSigner` to `signer` in the `getContractFactory` call produces the expected result (the code of the deployed contract)",
